olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 cucumber
2 clove garlic
2 tbs plain flour
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet pork schnitzels
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 tsp balsamic vinegar
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into wedges, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season and toss to coat. Bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.
• Meanwhile, grate carrot. Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons. Finely
chop garlic.

Little cooks: Older kids can help grate the carrot!

• In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and a good pinch of salt. In a
second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, combine panko
breadcrumbs, garlic & herb seasoning and garlic.
• Pull apart pork schnitzels so you get 2 per person. Coat pork in flour
mixture, followed by the egg and finally the panko breadcrumbs. Transfer
to a plate.

• When the wedges have 5 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over
high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base.
• Cook pork schnitzels until golden and cooked through, 1-2 minutes each
side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

• Meanwhile, combine mixed salad leaves, carrot, cucumber and a drizzle
of balsamic vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season and toss
to combine.
• Divide potato wedges, garlic and herb-crumbed pork and garden salad
between plates.
• Serve with dill & parsley mayonnaise. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the salad.